Feature 2 - Retailer Promotion and Discount System

In Sprint 2, we will also implement a promotion management system that allows the Nestlé admin to create promotional offers and push them directly to retailer homepages. The process will begin when the Nestlé admin logs into the admin dashboard and navigates to a “Promotions” section to create a new promotion. The admin will enter details such as the promotion title, discount value, applicable products, start date, expiry date, and promo code. The system will automatically generate a QR code based on the promo code. Once the promotion is published, it will become active and appear on the retailer homepage under an “Active Promotions” section.

Retailers will be able to view available promotions and use them during the ordering process. When placing an order, the retailer can either manually enter the promo code or scan the QR code to apply the promotion. The system will validate the promotion by checking whether the code exists, whether it is still within the valid time period, and whether it applies to the selected products. If valid, the discount will be applied to the order total before payment, and the retailer will proceed with payment as in the existing Sprint 1 workflow. If the promotion is expired or invalid, the system will show an error message and prevent its use. Expired promotions will automatically be removed from the retailer homepage. This feature will be considered complete when admins can create time-based promotions, retailers can view and apply them, and the system correctly validates and applies discounts before payment.